Pattern for parallel REST calls:

```java
// Launch calls in parallel
CompletableFuture<Escola> escolaFuture = 
    CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(() -> escolaClient.get(id), managedExecutor);
CompletableFuture<Turmas> turmasFuture = 
    CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(() -> turmaClient.list(id), managedExecutor);

// Wait for all and combine
CompletableFuture.allOf(escolaFuture, turmasFuture)
    .orTimeout(35, TimeUnit.SECONDS)
    .join();

Escola escola = escolaFuture.join();
Turmas turmas = turmasFuture.join();
```

Critical rules:
1. **Always use ManagedExecutorService** — not ForkJoinPool (loses CDI context)
2. **Timeout on the HTTP client** is the REAL protection (connect + read timeout)
3. **orTimeout()** is deadline safety net — does NOT cancel the underlying network call
4. **Handle failures per-future** — one failure shouldn't crash all
5. **Limit concurrency** — don't create one future per item in a 10,000-item list
